\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 Ingredients
\f1\b0\fs54 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 For Ginger syrup:
\f1\b0\fs54 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 4-inch piece ginger, peeled and roughly chopped\
1/2 cup sugar\
1 1/2 cups water\
Place all syrup ingredients in a saucepan and simmer until sugar dissolves and the ginger is infused in the syrup, about 20 minutes. Strain and allow to cool fully before use.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 For the drink:
\f1\b0\fs54 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 1 cup frozen cranberries\
1 lime, juiced\
2 cups vodka or gin\
2 cups cranberry juice\
1 cup ginger syrup, or to taste\
Splash club soda\
Shaved ginger\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 Directions
\f1\b0\fs54 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Crush the frozen cranberries in a large glass pitcher. Add the lime juice and their juiced wedges to the pitcher. Pour in the vodka, cranberry juice, and ginger syrup. Put ice in low-ball glasses and fill glasses about 2/3 full. Top off with club soda and garnish with a shaving of fresh ginger.\
Note: Can be made without soda for a martini.\
